body.p: Notice Of Judicial Election April 4, 1939 State of Wisconsin County of Monroe SS Notice is hereby given that at an election to be held in the several towns, wards, villages and election predicts on the first Tuesday of April, A. D., 1939, being the Fourth day of said month, the following officers are the be elected: A Justice of the Supreme Court, for bid term of ten years, to succeed Marvin B. Roseberry, whose term will expire on the first Monday of January A. D., 1940. Given under my hand and official seat at the Court House, in the City of Sparta, this 7th day of March, A. D., 1939. L. E. Austin County Clerk
